Haoran, what I said last time, 'Guard against arrogance and impetuosity; wealth means responsibility,' was not empty words. The higher your position, the more you need to settle down, work diligently, and take responsibility for those around you. That is the greatest wealth.

(From Feng Haoran to Gao Yunfei) Yunfei, today's run together was quite enjoyable. Speaking of this morning, I originally intended to run 6 kilometers to start the day off right, but I stayed up late studying last night and didn't get enough sleep, so my body felt a bit heavy. I ended up stopping after only 4 kilometers. Fortunately, this afternoon's run with you helped me regain much of my energy.

Haoran, your father has been diagnosed with acute cerebral infarction and is currently undergoing emergency treatment at Union Hospital. The doctor says an urgent surgery is needed. Please come back quickly!
Haoran, your father has been diagnosed with acute cerebral infarction and is currently undergoing emergency treatment at Union Hospital. The doctor says urgent surgery is required. Come back quickly!

After booking health checkup packages for my parents yesterday, I also reflected on myself. In terms of diet, I plan to start eating more vegetables and reduce ordering takeout. I should also schedule a health checkup for myself to see if there are suitable packages offered by the medical institutions that our company partners with.
Dear Aunt Chen, I am Feng Haoran. I sincerely invite you to attend my father's sixtieth birthday celebration in March. I look forward to your reply.

Coach Zhang, just finished training. My condition wasn't good today—my 5-kilometer run was noticeably slower than usual. I felt heavy and sluggish, probably due to the disruptions during the Spring Festival holiday. My sleep schedule is completely off.

Zhang Wei: Haoran, dinner at the usual place tonight, 7 p.m., can you make it?
Me: Sorry, I have a last-minute work arrangement to handle tonight, so I'll have to cancel the gathering. Hope you all have a great time!
【Digital RMB】Your purchase at BBK Supermarket on October 19, 2025, has been successfully completed with a Digital RMB red packet deduction.
President Huang, the itinerary has been confirmed. I will arrive in Shenzhen on time tomorrow. The meeting materials are prepared, and I look forward to our in-depth discussion in the afternoon.

Mom, is Dad's condition a bit more stable today? I just contacted the insurance agent and am preparing to select a medical insurance plan for you. This incident has made me think a lot—our family's financial safety net is too thin. I also need to make my own career planning more stable.
Today's discussion on the direction of space exploration has been preliminarily set as the topic of 'China's Space Achievements,' which requires further refinement.
Feng Haoran: I'm completely exhausted from climbing Mangshan Mountain today; my legs feel sore.
Feng Haoran: Finally, all packed up. The aftereffects from yesterday's mountain hike are really hitting me—every muscle in my body aches, and even packing up the tent was a struggle.
summarized_info: I texted Xie Yutong, mentioning that my muscles were sore after yesterday's hike and that packing up the tent was quite a struggle.

message_content: Schedule a traditional Chinese medicine massage and physical therapy service for tomorrow afternoon at 15:00.
contactName: Traditional Chinese Medicine Physical Therapy Center

message_content: Haoran, there's a particularly excellent stamp exhibition in Hangzhou next month. I heard it's themed around the early construction of New China, featuring many rare items seldom seen on the market. I plan to attend. Are you interested?

I checked the high-speed rail tickets, and it's quite convenient to travel from Shenzhen to Hangzhou East. The exhibition is at the Hangzhou International Convention and Exhibition Center, starting on April 10th and lasting for a week.

Haoran, our unit recently filmed a promotional video at the Meixi Lake International Culture and Arts Center. The architectural lines there are particularly suitable for someone like you who enjoys street photography.

By the way, if you go out to take photos this weekend, you could also visit the Xie Zilong Image Art Museum. There's currently a photography exhibition on urban transformation, which I think you would enjoy.
Haoran, I've been working on a new project recently—designing the entire visual system for the Pengwei P80 Pro. It’s quite a challenge, but I think you’ll appreciate the color scheme and icon style.

By the way, I mentioned to you before that I was involved in designing a smartphone. My friend, a photographer, took a series of sample photos using the engineering prototype, and the results are absolutely stunning! It's the Pengwei P80 Pro. You might want to keep an eye out for the official promotional materials that will follow.

Haoran, our running plan for tomorrow morning may need to be adjusted. The section of Lushan South Road we often run on seems to be undergoing underground pipeline network construction, with a large area cordoned off and the road surface covered in mud.

The section of Lushan South Road we mentioned last time is still under construction. We can start from the Dongfanghong Square at Hunan University, then detour to Pailou Road. The scenery there is also quite nice, though it tends to be more crowded.

Consultant Feng, our company is evaluating a public welfare investment project in the ESG field. It involves collaborating with universities to organize an environmental innovation challenge, with a focus on the practical implementation of technology.

The name of the competition mentioned last time has been officially finalized as the "Zero-Carbon Future" Youth Science and Technology Innovation Challenge. We plan to establish a dedicated fund to support the winning teams.

Bro! My advanced training course ended earlier than expected. I've booked a flight back home on the evening of October 25th, landing in Shanghai. After resting for a day, I'll head back to Changsha to meet up with you all!

I checked the high-speed train schedule and can arrive at Changsha South Station on the afternoon of the 26th. Let's set it for the evening of the 26th. Invite Sister Yuqing and the others, and we can have a good gathering to celebrate my successful completion of studies! You choose the location—you know I love Hunan cuisine.

I've hit a bit of a bottleneck with street photography lately, so I'm thinking of switching cities to find some inspiration. After looking at some photos, I feel the three-dimensional quality and lively atmosphere of a mountain city really suit my style. It's decided—that's my next destination.

Do you remember that mountain city project you mentioned wanting to shoot back in April? I recently came across a series of photos taken in Chongqing—the play of light and shadow along with the composition is absolutely stunning, a perfect example of exactly the kind of vibe you described!
Lao Luo, any new developments in the market lately? I heard a batch of old stamps has surfaced.

Indeed, there is talk within the circle about a newly discovered set of 1953 blue commemorative stamps in excellent condition. Reportedly, they were issued in limited quantities to mark a significant event of that time, and very few remain today. The name itself carries distinct characteristics of the era—"People's Victory." Would you be interested in looking into it?

The blue "People's Victory" commemorative stamp you mentioned last time is indeed listed in this year's Guardian Autumn Auction catalog! The estimated price is quite high. Unfortunately, I'm just looking.
Mr. Shen, have you brought in any interesting new beans recently? I'm craving some.

What a coincidence! We just received a batch of auction-grade beans, and there's one you're sure to love—it's a winning lot from this year's BOP (Best of Panama), with exceptionally complex flavor layers. I won't spoil the name; come and let it surprise you.

Last time you asked about the BOP-winning coffee beans, which are the Geisha variety from Panama's Hacienda La Esmeralda, washed process. Today, I adjusted the brewing parameters, and the floral and apricot-peach notes became more prominent. Feel free to come and try it when you have time.
Xiaoyu, do you have any camping plans for the second half of the year? I heard there might be an event in Hunan.

Yes! There's a stargazing-themed camping event in Hunan at the end of September, held at a World Natural Heritage site with Danxia landforms in Shaoyang. It's said the night sky there is absolutely stunning, and I've already signed up.

The notice regarding the postponement of the previously mentioned camping event in Hunan has been released. Due to major maintenance at the Langshan Scenic Area in October, the event has been rescheduled to early November.

Mr. Qian, regarding the new energy case I shared during today's review meeting, the client suffered a 15% loss of their total capital because they did not follow the advice on diversifying investments. Instead, they heavily invested in a startup focused on a single technological path, which was later proven to be unviable, resulting in the company's stock price dropping to zero.

The case you mentioned in March, which incurred a 15% loss, serves as a significant warning. I recently met with Mr. Lin, and he also brought up this matter, mentioning that the client was a friend he had referred. Initially, the client invested 5 million yuan in principal and now deeply regrets it.

Mom, I suddenly remembered that you took me to a huge aquarium when I was little. There was a very long underwater tunnel inside. It felt so magical back then. What was it called? I kind of want to go see it again.

Are you referring to the one at Wuhan East Lake? It's called 'East Lake Ocean World'. You were only five or six years old at that time and refused to leave after playing there. Why do you suddenly think of this?

I went back to Wuhan for the Chinese New Year and visited the East Lake Ocean World you mentioned. It has been renovated, and the underwater tunnel is still there, but it doesn't seem as big as I remember from my childhood.

【Luo Zhenyu】Haoran, happy New Year! Have you seen the stamp catalog? The first new stamp set of 2025 is about to be issued. I heard the design is quite unique, featuring a regional cultural theme. I've already asked someone to reserve a set for me.

【Feng Haoran】Happy New Year, Brother Luo! I've seen the catalog. This set of designs is truly excellent, with thoughtful composition and color schemes. I have already placed an order to reserve a set.

【Feng Xinran】Bro, you've been in Changsha for so many years. Could you recommend some representative natural attractions? Our company is working on a promotional video about Huxiang culture and we're looking for some material and inspiration.

【Feng Haoran】There are far too many to list. Besides the classics like Yuelu Mountain, Orange Isle, and Zhangjiajie, even postage stamps have recently been promoting the 'Hunan Scenery' theme. A set of four stamps includes several scenes from the Eight Views of Xiaoxiang. You can take a look at the design of that stamp set for inspiration.

【Huang Siqi】Consultant Feng, I have reviewed the underlying asset analysis report for the XX Real Estate Investment Trust you recommended last week, and it indeed shows potential. However, I have an investment repayment expected to arrive early next week. Once the funds are in place, I will proceed with the subscription immediately.
【Feng Haoran】Understood, Mr. Huang. I will reserve the credit line for you, and we will proceed with the operation as soon as the funds are in place.

【Zheng Wenbo】Haoran, your client Mr. Huang in Shenzhen acted really fast. He just mentioned last week that the funds would arrive, and this week he already transferred 3 million. I've just completed the process for the product contract.

【Feng Haoran】Indeed, President Huang has always been highly efficient in execution. She contacted me as soon as the funds were credited last Wednesday (May 12th), so we need to keep up with the process as well.

【Xu Jianing】Haoran, regarding the specialty coffee shop you mentioned last time you were in Shenzhen, I found an exceptional one called 'Tihu' in OCT-LOFT. Their pour-over Geisha is absolutely amazing, with remarkably clear flavor layers. You must give it a try.
【Feng Haoran】Noted, 'Tihu', hand-brewed Geisha. Will definitely visit when I go to Shenzhen next time, and share tasting notes with you afterward.

【Shen Xinyi】Mr. Feng, I heard from industry friends that there's a shop in Shenzhen called 'Tihu' that selects its beans quite well. In addition to regular pour-over coffee, their creative specialty drinks are quite innovative, blending tea, spices, and coffee seamlessly, which has become another signature offering.

【Feng Haoran】Thank you for the recommendation, Mr. Shen. I recently heard about this place from another friend as well. It seems it has a really good reputation in the industry. I've noted down both the Geisha coffee and the creative specialty drinks.
【Feng Jianguo】Son, your birthday is coming up. Your mom and I bought you a gift, something you've been saying you really like. We mailed it out today, and it should arrive in Changsha tomorrow.
Feng Haoran: Thanks, Dad! Still keeping it a secret, huh? Let me guess. Looking forward to receiving it tomorrow!
【Gao Yunfei】I saw you brought a new camera during your morning run today. It looks really cool, is that the new Leica SL3? How's the image quality and handling?

【Feng Haoran】 You have a keen eye—it is indeed the SL3. It was a birthday gift from my father, and I've just started using it. The build feels solid, and the response speed is faster than expected. The colors still have that classic Leica look. I'm looking forward to trying it out with some street photography.

【Qian Yongqiang】Xiao Feng, I heard there's a new Hunan restaurant that just opened on Furong Middle Road near the company. The owner is a master chef from Changde, specializing in traditional cooking techniques. I plan to try it out this weekend. If the flavors are authentic, we can book it for our next team gathering.
【Feng Haoran】Understood, Mr. Qian. We look forward to your store review. Master Changde's pot dishes and stewed rice noodles are truly exceptional.

【Peng Yuqing】Haoran! Didn't you mention last time that Mr. Qian recommended a new Hunan restaurant? Is it called 'Xiangjiang Chunxiao'? My friend went there yesterday and said their chopped chili fish head and Changde beef stew with rice noodles are absolutely amazing—highly recommended.
【Feng Haoran】Yes, this is the one! President Qian tried the dishes there last week, and it seems the feedback was quite positive. Now we have a venue for the gathering.

【Xie Yutong】Haoran, I've been thinking about upgrading my tent recently. After reading a lot of reviews, I'm really drawn to a lightweight two-person tent. It's freestanding and packs down small, which seems perfect for our style of camping where we often have to hike a bit. You know a lot about gear—what do you think?

【Feng Haoran】You're referring to the MSR Hubba Hubba NX 2, right? It indeed has an excellent reputation, featuring a classic tunnel tent design with a good balance between weight and space. Its wind and rain resistance is considered outstanding among similar products. The only drawback is that the price isn't very friendly.

【Zhou Yuwei】Haoran, I'm planning to go hiking and camping during the National Day holiday and am currently looking at gear. You mentioned a two-person tent called MSR... something before. What's the full model name? I want to search for reviews.

【Feng Haoran】MSR Hubba Hubba NX 2. I just discussed this model with another camping friend last week. It offers comprehensive performance, though it's a bit pricey. You might want to check out the Access series from the same brand, which is slightly more affordable.

Brother Haoran, I've booked a ticket to return to Changsha at the end of April and plan to stay for about three days. Besides wanting to capture some shots of the new look of the old streets, I mainly want to attend that event. I think you might be interested too, right?
Jianing said she will definitely come, as she also took many photos of old streets when she studied in Changsha. Now the three of us photography enthusiasts can finally gather together.
Mr. Shen, please remember to reserve two tickets for the opening ceremony for me. I'll be going with Xu Jianing. What a coincidence—she happens to be returning at the end of this month.
No problem! The "Ichigo Ichie" City Memory Coffee Photography Exhibition will open at my café at 3 PM on April 28th. See you then!

Hao Ran, I've been feeling uncomfortable and sweaty with in-ear headphones during my morning runs lately. I'm thinking of switching to open-ear headphones, and I've heard bone conduction ones are good—they allow you to listen to music while staying safe. Which brand do you think I should buy?

The 'Shaoyin' brand headphones you recommended back then, specifically the AfterShokz Aeropex model, I've checked the reviews, and they have a high waterproof and sweatproof rating, making them really suitable for running. I'm planning to get a pair. Thanks!

Haoran, there's a hot topic in the stamp market recently—a special set of stamps themed 'Tea' is about to be issued. The design is exceptionally exquisite, and I've been following it for a long time. Do you have any updates on this?

I visited the stamp market today and saw a new set of stamps featuring "Dongting Biluochun" tea. The design is truly elegant. As Lao Luo mentioned before, this should be the one. The market is on an upward trend—would you like to get a set as well?
Yes, it's exactly the set that Brother Luo mentioned. I have already asked someone to reserve two sets for me—one for collection and the other for preparing a stamp album.

Haoran, there will be an internal lecture on the new regulations for digital currency investment next Thursday afternoon, featuring experts from the headquarters. The venue remains the usual place. Please inform the colleagues in our group and ensure their attendance.
Ajie, there will be a lecture at our company's training center on Thursday afternoon. Shall I find you for a meal after it ends?
Sure. Is this the Huatai Securities Training Center? About what time will the lecture end?

Mr. Feng, we have received information that there will be a high-end closed-door forum on "AI Empowering Primary Market Investment" in Shenzhen next week. The event is of a high caliber. I believe you might be interested and suggest keeping an eye on it.
Xiaoya, please help me check the detailed agenda and guest list for the AI investment forum in Shenzhen next Wednesday. Also, has President Huang confirmed his attendance?
Hao Ran, the agenda has been sent to your email. The forum will take place all day on April 23 (next Wednesday). Ms. Siqi Huang has confirmed her participation as a panelist.

Haoran, are you free on the evening of the first day of the May Day holiday? Wenjing has also returned from Shanghai, so shall we get together? I heard there's a newly opened Hunan restaurant that is quite good, and I'd like to try it.
Wenjing, the dinner on the evening of May 1st is scheduled at "Xiangju Lou." Yuqing recommended it, saying it's newly opened and the food is authentic. We'll meet there directly at 6:30 p.m.
Received! Finally, I can have authentic Hunan cuisine. Let me see where 'Xiang Ju Lou' is. Is it the one Yuqing mentioned last time? Looking forward to it!

Hello Jianing, here is the complete collection link for "Night Talks on the Xiang River," which I have organized as per our café arrangement. I would appreciate hearing your professional feedback at your convenience—there is no rush. Thank you!
【JD.com】Christmas & New Year Gifting Season! Plan your gift budget in advance and enjoy exclusive offers.
Feng Xinran: Brother, I've arrived in Changsha. This visit has been really enjoyable, and I'm looking forward to the photos you took for me!

Apple Customer Service: Hello, regarding the screen damage on your iPhone 14 Pro, the official repair cost is estimated at ¥2599. Since the internal screen displays colored stripes and the touch function is completely unresponsive, there may be other components involved. We recommend bringing the device to the store for further inspection, as the cost could potentially be higher.
Haoran: Jianing, regarding the collaboration on the photography exhibition, we need to meet in person to discuss the details. When are you available next week? Let's schedule a time to meet and talk.
Jianing: Haoran, I've finalized the meeting time and location as we discussed yesterday. I'll send you the specific details in your schedule later.
Wu Junjie: Haoran, we've arrived at the Hunan restaurant. Have you set off yet?
The interior of the refrigerator has been wiped and the rubber seal of the washing machine has been cleaned as planned, with satisfactory results.
Wenbo, the reading insights I shared during lunch today were based on that book about behavioral biases from my notes. I look forward to our further discussion.

Me: Brother Lei, I really enjoyed yesterday's gathering. I also did a lot of thinking while running today, about the future. I feel clearer about my priorities now, and I'm ready to give it my all going forward.

Mr. Qian, hello. I saw the announcement about our colleague Sun Xiaoya's promotion, and I've been having some thoughts about my own career development recently. I would like to find an opportunity to discuss this with you. Would you be available after lunch today?

Yunfei, during dinner I discussed the idea of the investment research meeting with Yutong. Drawing from her experience in cultural and creative projects, she offered a fresh perspective. The notes I organized yesterday proved useful.

Me: Yunfei, thanks for the breakfast you treated me to this morning. I've been thinking more about the entry points we discussed for incorporating periodic running data into a personal health management system, and I found it quite inspiring. The data from next weekend's run around Meixi Lake will be perfect for putting this into practice.

(To the 'Family Group') Mom, Dad, Xinran, regarding the in-depth physical examination to be discussed in tomorrow's video conference, I have organized and shared in the group the comparison reports of several physical examination institution packages previously collected, as well as materials on the necessity of preventing cardiovascular and cerebrovascular diseases. Please take a look when you have time. Especially considering Dad's previous condition, I believe the in-depth physical examination is highly valuable. Tomorrow, we will discuss the details and see if we can schedule it for March or April next year.
Mom, I'm staying with Dad at the Wuhan hospital these days, and I have to handle work matters simultaneously. It's quite urgent.
Haoran, the performance review results are out. Xiaoya performed exceptionally well this time. We need to step up our game in this batch.
Peng Yuqing: How was the review session yesterday? Do you have a clear plan for next year?

I: It's been very fruitful, and my thinking is much clearer now. Several major directions have been decided, especially the matter of the pension account, which has been incorporated into the plan and is set to be launched in the first quarter.

Dad, Mom, I've selected the medical check-up institution, and it's Meinian Onehealth. It's a nationwide chain with branches in both Wuhan and Changsha, making cross-city services very convenient. You can get examined in Wuhan, and I can follow up in Changsha.

Xinran: Bro, I've taken a quick look at the pension plan you sent me. It's a bit complicated, but the overall idea seems really good! Dad has asked about similar things before, but I never quite understood them. You'll have to explain it to me properly when we meet this weekend!

Feng Haoran: Mom, based on this year's health review, we have decided to arrange comprehensive physical examinations for the whole family. We have already scheduled an appointment at Central Hospital for next month. I will send you the specific details later.
Feng Haoran: While volunteering today, our neighbor Aunt Chen shared many historical anecdotes about Yuelu Mountain, giving me a whole new understanding of the cultural heritage of Changsha.
Colleague Wang: Is the salon over? Don't forget about tomorrow's event.
To Peng Yuqing: During the lunch break, I scrolled through my phone and saw everyone in the close friends group liking and commenting on the short video shared yesterday, so I gave a brief reply.

Jianing, good morning. I took some night shots by the Xiang River last night and just finished processing them in Lightroom. I've picked five that I think are decent and have sent you the comparison images of the original and edited versions via email. Could you take a look?

Haoran, I've reviewed the photos. The overall atmosphere is good, but for some of the long-exposure shots, the exposure time could be extended a bit further to make the light trails smoother. You could also experiment with more angles in your compositions. I've sent you detailed suggestions via email.
Brother Yun, as we discussed earlier, the field trip plan for this afternoon remains unchanged. Let's meet at the usual time and place. I have brought all the equipment.

Zhang Chen: Haoran, it was a pleasure meeting you at last week's workshop. The lighting in that set of portraits you shot was excellent. Regarding the outdoor shoot we discussed earlier, are you available this weekend? Li Wei mentioned she would like to join as well.

Friend: Are you going to the public open day at Kanai Observatory tonight?  
Me: Yes, I've already signed up. I'm really looking forward to the observation session.
Feng Haoran: Just attended the premium coffee bean tasting event at Xinyi Café, tried three rare varieties, excellent!
